we can use existing tools to create a prototype of Comshell;

; sudo pacman -S xorg-server xorg-xinit xf86-video-{intel,nouveau,amdgpu} compton i3-wm
; sudo pacman -S emacs chromium mpv

; nano ~/.bash_profile
  startx
; nano ~/.xinitrc
  exec i3
; mkdir -p ~/.config/i3
; cp prototype/i3.config ~/.config/i3/config

; mkdir ~/.emacs.d
; cp prototype/*.el ~/.emacs.d/
ELisp is terrible as a programming language,
  but it's pretty good as a command_line interface (ie as a shell, like Bash);

; mkdir -p ~/.config/gtk-3.0
; nano ~/.config/gtk-3.0/gtk.css
  GtkScrollbar {}

user scripts:
  https://github.com/fanglingsu/vimb/tree/master/src/scripts
  https://surf.suckless.org/files/link_hints/
  https://surf.suckless.org/files/easier_key/
user style sheets:
  // show scrollbar on the left;
  .parent {
    overflow: auto;
    transform: scaleX(-1);
  }
  .sleeve {
    transform: scaleX(-1);
  }
